set_pixel() - DERP OS man page

Name -------------------
set_pixel() - set_pixel sets a pixel in the given screen buffer

Synopsis ---------------

#include "gl.h"

void set_pixel_int  ( Uint32 x, Uint32 y, Uint32 p, screen_info* curr_si );
void set_pixel      ( Uint32 x, Uint32 y, pixel p, screen_info* curr_si );

Description ------------

THe set_pixel function sets the pixel at the given x and y position inside of the
given screen_info/screen buffer. The function sets the pixel to the color givin
as a pixel struct(p) or as a Uint32(p).

Return Value -----------

No return value, but the side effect should be a pixel of color (p) in the 
screen buffer.
